.\" shell.1 - manual page for shell
.TH SHELL 1 "July 2026" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shell \- determine current shell and its properties
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shell
displays information about the current shell environment.
It detects the shell name, version, process ID, executable path,
and history availability.
.PP
The detection works for:
.B bash, zsh, fish, ksh, dash, sh, ash, tcsh, csh, yash
and other shells that appear in the process list.
.SH OUTPUT
.TP 12
.B Shell
The name of the current shell (e.g., bash, zsh, fish).
.TP
.B Version
Shell version if available.
.TP
.B PID
Process ID of the shell.
.TP
.B Executable
Path to the shell executable (if accessible).
.TP
.B History
Whether history commands (fc/history) are available.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B shell
Shell: bash
Version: 5.2.15(1)-release
PID: 12345
Executable: /usr/bin/bash
History: available
.SH NOTES
For fish shell, the script uses
.B $fish_pid
instead of $$ to correctly detect the process.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Serg (serg@serg-X540UA)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR echo (1), ps (1), basename (1)
